main event: A civilian reported observing a white, star-like object moving in circular movements near Detroit Lakes, Minnesota on April 1, 1953.
interesting points: The object was observed for approximately 15 minutes., The object appeared to move rapidly and then simply vanished., The report lacks physical evidence or photographs., The weather was overcast at the time of the sighting., The witness had no prior experience in aircraft recognition.
sighted object: a small white colored star-like object
